'It is not enough to remember the fallen, we must honour them. Before the Enemy came to our lands, we kept Langraf pristine, but with the never-ending battles in the field, it has fallen into disrepair. Worse yet, it has become infested.\n\n'Head into Langraf and clean out the gredbyg and rats that you find lurking within. Our ancestors deserve better than we have given them.'
'One day, Langraf will be restored to its full glory.'
'Few outsiders have ever wandered the halls of Langraf.'\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>This is an instanced public questing area.</rgb>
Langraf has fallen into disrepair and gredbyg have filled the tombs.

Gredbyg and rats can be found at Langraf.\n\nWaldeg has asked you to venture within Langraf and clean out the gredbyg and rats found within.
Waldeg is at Snowbourn.\n\nWaldeg will be pleased to hear you have helped to clean the gredbyg and rats out of Langraf.
